Boil the @water{300%ml} in a large #saucepan{} over high heat. Add the @basmati rice{150%g}, half the @vegetable stock pot{1} and the @star anise{1}. Stir to dissolve the stock pot then cover with a #lid{}, lower the heat to medium and cook for ~{10%minutes}. Remove from the heat and set aside for another ~{10%minutes}. The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced) into half moons. Peel and grate the @ginger{1%piece}(peeled and grated). Halve, then remove the core from the @red pepper{1}(halved and chopped into 2cm pieces) and chop into 2cm pieces. Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1}(halved lengthways then sliced into 1cm wide half moons). Cut in half lengthways then slice into 1cm wide half moons. Trim the tops from the @green beans{1%bunch}(trimmed and chopped in half) and chop in half. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped).

Put a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the onion and cook, stirring, until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Add the ginger and @yellow Thai style paste{1}(yellow curry paste) along with a pinch of @?sugar{} and cook, still stirring, for another ~{1%minute}. Add the rest of the veggies, along with the @coconut milk{400%ml} and remaining stock pot. Stir to dissolve the stock pot, then simmer until thickened, ~{10%minutes}.

While the curry cooks, put another frying pan on high heat and add the @cashew nuts{25}(toasted, no oil). Toast until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}. Shake the pan often.

> TIP: Watch your nuts like a hawk as they burn easily!

Remove from the pan and set aside.

When the curry is cooked, stir through the @soy sauce{1.5%tbsp} and add a squeeze of @lime{1/2}(juiced). Taste and add more lime juice if desired. Fluff the rice up with a #fork{} and remove the star anise.

Serve the rice in #bowls{} with a generous portion of Indonesian curry on top. Finish by sprinkling over the chopped coriander and toasted cashew nuts. Enjoy!